# Z-Sanctuary: Canvas & Master Control

When working in **ZSanctuary_Universe** (or any Z-Sanctuary context):

## Canvas as the control surface

- If the user has a **Cursor Canvas** open for this project (e.g. "Z-Sanctuary Master"), treat it as the **single surface** for the Master Register, Full Build Checklist, and "Our best" priorities. Use the Canvas context when deciding what to add, upgrade, or simplify.
- If no Canvas is open, still use the **docs** as the source of truth: [docs/Z-MASTER-MODULES-REGISTER.md](docs/Z-MASTER-MODULES-REGISTER.md) and [docs/Z-FULL-BUILD-CHECKLIST.md](docs/Z-FULL-BUILD-CHECKLIST.md).

## Register and checklist

- Before adding or changing a **module**, **core engine**, or **panel**: check the Master Register and (if applicable) the Full Build Checklist. Update the register or checklist when something is implemented or deprecated.
- When **simplifying**: merge or consolidate in the register first, then in code.
- **Triple-check** workflow: folders/datasets, upgrade what we have, implement what we don’t, simplify without dropping ideas. See Register §9.

## Operational roof and hierarchy

- Keep **Z-Super Overseer AI** (Z-EAII + auto-run + Z-SSWS) as the single operational roof. Do not add tasks or ports that conflict with the Overseer doc (Organiser: `docs/Z-SUPER-OVERSEER-AI.md`) or the registry.
- **When unsure** about architecture, module placement, or cross-project impact: check [docs/Z-HIERARCHY-CHIEF-AND-OBSERVER-VIEW.md](docs/Z-HIERARCHY-CHIEF-AND-OBSERVER-VIEW.md) first (Hierarchy Chief). See also `.cursor/rules/z-hierarchy-chief.mdc`.

## Dashboard and Blueprint

- The dashboard’s **Z Blueprint** panel links to the same Register, Checklist, and INDEX. Any change to "Our best" priorities or to linked docs should stay consistent with what the Blueprint panel shows (see [docs/Z-CURSOR-CANVAS-GUIDE.md](docs/Z-CURSOR-CANVAS-GUIDE.md)).

## Benefits

- **Canvas + this rule** = full integration of "manage all & everything" into Cursor workflows.
- **Z Blueprint panel** in the dashboard = same control centre from the app. Together they keep the Sanctuary fully managed and ensure nothing is left out.
